t remaining 9 silicone moulds aside."},{"content":"Place a piece of wet and well-wrung baking paper, then a piece of paper towel, on top of the puddings in Varoma dish and tray. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>18-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until puddings are cooked. Remove Varoma and place puddings into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Place Varoma back into position and repeat with remaining 9 silicone moulds, covering again with a piece of wet and well-wrung baking paper, followed by a piece of paper towel. Secure Varoma lid, then repeat steaming <b>18-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until puddings are cooked."},{"content":"Serve puddings warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Baked chocolate and prune pudding:<\/strong> In step 6, transfer batter into a round baking dish (1300 mL capacity). Bake in the oven for 30 minutes at 160°C, then cover with aluminium foil and bake for a further 30-45 minutes (160°C) or until a wooden skewer comes out clean.","Serve warm puddings with <em>Brandy cream<\/em> or <em>Brandy butter<\/em>. For a decadent chocolate dessert make a Chocolate ganache to drizzle over the top (see <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>).","Puddings can be made up to 1-2 weeks prior to Christmas, then frozen. Remove puddings from freezer 1 hour before serving. Place 500 g water into mixing bowl and steam <strong>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong> to heat puddings to serve."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 30m","18 portions"]}